<div class="title">Behavioral Design Patterns</div>
<img src="https://i.stack.imgur.com/tLbXm.png" class="state" alt="state machine">
<p>Behavioral pabberns show up primarily when behavior should affect a large number of objects. They may make it so that communication happens more easily, as with the mediator, or so that programs can easily complete operations across a number of objects, as with the itterator. They may even make objects behave differently at different times when interacted with in the same way.(<a href="https://sourcemaking.com/design_patterns/behavioral_patterns">source</a>)</p> 
